The last line multiplies this matrix by $x$ to get the next powers.
$$
\begin{bmatrix}
u_{n+1}\\
v_{n+1}\\
x_{n+1}
\end{bmatrix}
=
\begin{bmatrix}
2x & u_n & 0\\
-x & 2x & v_n\\
0 & -x & 2x\\
\end{bmatrix}
\begin{bmatrix}
u_n\\
v_n\\
x_{n}
\end{bmatrix}
$$
Given the initial values $(u_0,v_0,x_0)=(1,1/6,1)$ in a piece of paper, you can create a polyglot simulation chasing a virtual turtle, starting at $(1,1/6,1)$, then repeatedly drawing one step forward incident to the previous step. 
The virtual turtle ends up moving in a fixed direction if and only if it explores the entire plane timably.

